      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's new\n\n### New tokens\n- `{{ track_popularity }}` — Spotify popularity score for the track (0–100), no extra API call\n- `{{ album_popularity }}` — Spotify popularity score for the album (0–100), fetches `GET /v1/albums/{id}` only when the token is present in the template\n\n### Bug fix: genre deduplication\nGenres are now correctly deduplicated across all artists. Previously, `new Set()` was applied to arrays (reference equality), so shared genres were not removed. Affects `{{ genres }}`, `{{ genres_array }}`, and `{{ genres_hashtag }}`.\n\n### Get track by Spotify ID or URL\nTwo new commands that accept a full Spotify track URL or bare track ID via a modal prompt — no need for the track to be currently playing:\n- **Append track by Spotify ID or URL using template** — inserts into the active note\n- **Create file for track by Spotify ID or URL using template** — creates a new file using the song template\n\n### Context menu improvements\n- Right-clicking a **folder** now correctly shows plugin menu items (previously only files worked)\n- Right-clicking a **file** now creates the note in the file's parent folder instead of an invalid path\n- New **Context Menu** section in settings to toggle each item individually\n- New items added in future versions are automatically merged into existing settings — no manual reset required\n- **Create file for track by Spotify ID or URL** added to the context menu (disabled by default, opt-in via settings)\n\n### Settings\n- **Clear Spotify session** button in the Reset section — removes stored tokens from localStorage to force a full re-authentication\n- Song template description updated to mention it is also used by the \"by ID or URL\" commands\n- Fixed stale `{{ artist_names }}` token reference in the settings token list → `{{ artist_name }}`\n\n### Docs\n- Updated token reference, context menu section, troubleshooting (429 rate limiting)",
